HEADWORD: pan out
<hw>pan` out"</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧n`out")</pr>, <sn>1.</sn> <pos>v. i.</pos>
<def>To succeed; <as>as, the project didn't <ex>pan
out</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To turn out (profitably or unprofitably); to result;
to develop; <as>as, the investigation, or the speculation, <ex>panned
out</ex> poorly</as>.</def> <mark>[Slang, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Panpharmacon</ent>⟦br⟧
